article.headline: Cleveland St. 77, Chicago St. 73
article.story: CHICAGO (AP) -- Joe Davis scored a team-high 18 points to lead Cleveland State to a 77-73 victory over Chicago State on Tuesday night. Chris Moore had 17 points and eight rebounds and J'Nathan Bullock added 14 points for the Vikings (6-3), who never trailed in the second half but had a hard time shaking Chicago State (3-7). The Cougars held Cleveland State leading scorer Cedric Jackson to six points, but he had a game-high eight assists and a pair of steals. David Holston scored a game-high 19 points for Chicago State. John Cantrell added 17 points. The Cougars had a chance to tie the game at 76 but Steve Martin missed a 3-pointer with less than a minute remaining. The Cougars had 27 points off turnovers, compared with 15 for Chicago State. Cleveland State's bench also outscored the Chicago State bench 31-21. The Vikings led 40-36 at the half.
